    <p class="text-gray-700">Look for pale salmon or onion-skin pink colors rather than bright magenta, which often indicates lower quality or added coloring. Premium rosé producers like Domaines Ott, Château d'Esclans, or Sancerre rosé typically use clear or antique glass bottles to showcase the wine's delicate hue. Check for specific vineyard designations, harvest dates, and avoid bottles with cartoon-like labels or overly saturated pink packaging, which often signal mass-produced, sweet styles.</p>
